The price of bread in  Chile  may rise
by as much as 38 percent, Television Nacional  reported , after
increases in the cost of flour and fuel for ovens.  Bread may gain to 1,100 pesos a kilo from 800 pesos a kilo,
the television channel said, citing bakery owners. Chileans are
the worldâ€™s second-biggest consumers of bread, the state-owned
channel, known as TVN from its initials in Spanish, reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
